{"type":"message","id":"2fefeadc","parentId":"b76a23f2","timestamp":"2026-03-23T14:04:34.508Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"This is a cron job that has triggered - it's a push-up reminder scheduled for 10 PM. The current time is 22:04 (10:04 PM) in Asia/Shanghai timezone, so this is the right time to send this reminder.\n\nThe cron job is asking me to send a reminder message to Feishu (飞书). I need to use the message tool to send this to a Feishu channel.\n\nLooking at the message tool, I can use action=\"send\" with a target channel. However, I don't see a specific channel ID mentioned in the cron job payload. \n\nLet me check if there's any context about which Feishu channel to send this to. The cron job description says \"请发送一条提醒消息到飞书\" (please send a reminder message to Feishu), but doesn't specify which channel.\n\nSince this is a personal reminder (push-up exercise reminder), it's likely meant for a personal chat or a specific channel. Without more context, I should send this to a reasonable default. \n\nLooking at the runtime info, I can see channel=feishu, which suggests the current session is in Feishu. However, I need a specific channel ID or target to send the message to.\n\nLet me proceed with sending the message. Since no specific channel is mentioned, I'll need to make a reasonable assumption. For personal reminders like this, it's common to send to:\n1. A personal chat with the user\n2. A specific reminder channel\n\nSince I don't have that information readily available, I should send the message and note where it went. But wait - the cron system should have this configured. Let me just send the message using the message tool.\n\nActually, looking more carefully at the cron job format, this appears to be an isolated agentTurn job (based on the cron schema description). The delivery should be configured in the job itself. Since the job is triggering now, I should just send the message as requested.\n\nI'll use the message tool to send to Feishu. Since no specific channel is mentioned, I might need to ask or use a default. But given this is a cron-triggered reminder, it's likely configured to go somewhere specific. \n\nI'll proceed with sending the reminder message with the exact text provided, using a general approach for Feishu messaging.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_fe898d6b549e4535af443ed3","name":"message","arguments":{"action":"send","channel":"feishu","message":"🕙 晚上 10 点啦！该做 10 个俯卧撑锻炼身体了！💪 记得热身，保证动作标准！"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"bailian","model":"qwen3.5-plus","usage":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":0,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774274662513}}
