{"type":"message","id":"894a0c1c","parentId":"392dff03","timestamp":"2026-03-23T14:04:40.846Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The message tool requires a target parameter. I need to specify where to send this message. Since this is a cron job for a personal reminder, it should likely go to the user's Feishu chat or a specific channel.\n\nSince I don't have the specific channel ID from the cron job context, I should check if there's a way to determine the target. Let me try sending to a general target or check what channels are available.\n\nActually, looking at the cron job ID \"a21d9459-c51d-4eaf-8fee-bdecc8e1a5ca\" and name \"俯卧撑提醒\", this was set up earlier with a specific target in mind. Since I don't have that context readily available, I should try to send to the user directly or ask.\n\nBut wait - for a cron-triggered reminder like this, the delivery should have been configured when the job was created. Let me try using the message tool with a more generic approach. \n\nSince this is Feishu and it's a personal reminder, I could try sending without specifying a channel (which might default to the current context), or I need to figure out the right target.\n\nLet me try sending the message without the channel parameter, just using target instead.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_a607346518e34d0499d0ec2c","name":"message","arguments":{"action":"send","target":"feishu","message":"🕙 晚上 10 点啦！该做 10 个俯卧撑锻炼身体了！💪 记得热身，保证动作标准！"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"bailian","model":"qwen3.5-plus","usage":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":0,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774274674543}}
